HEADWORD: Protractive
<hw>Pro*tract"ive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Drawing out or
lengthening in time; prolonging; continuing; delaying.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He suffered their <qex>protractive</qex> arts.</q>
